WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.416 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.416 --> 00:00:12.896 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:12.896 --> 00:00:18.380 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.380 --> 00:00:22.290 align:middle line:84%
>> The cosmic dance
of spirit and matter,

00:00:22.290 --> 00:00:28.200 align:middle line:84%
of transcendence and eminence,
of heaven and Earth, masculine,

00:00:28.200 --> 00:00:30.480 align:middle line:84%
feminine, in breath
and out breath.

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:35.200 align:middle line:90%


00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:39.250 align:middle line:84%
>> We become part of the
whole and achieve yoga, union.

00:00:39.250 --> 00:00:50.850 align:middle line:90%


00:00:50.850 --> 00:00:54.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Union consciousness, or
the amalgamation of opposites,

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:57.400 align:middle line:90%
is a foundational force in yoga.

00:00:57.400 --> 00:01:00.640 align:middle line:84%
Hatha yoga utilizes
this force of opposites

00:01:00.640 --> 00:01:03.460 align:middle line:84%
to create balance and
awaken dormant energy

00:01:03.460 --> 00:01:07.283 align:middle line:84%
through breath, postures,
and meditation techniques.

