Tha is the moon.

00:01:10.940 --> 00:01:14.590 align:middle line:84%
To bring those equal and
opposite forces in equilibrium,

00:01:14.590 --> 00:01:18.700 align:middle line:84%
in balance, in
harmony is Hatha yoga.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:24.250 align:middle line:84%
It is one of the ancient forms
of mostly physical practice

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:25.840 align:middle line:90%
part of yoga.

00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:31.480 align:middle line:84%
So Hatha yoga includes asana,
pranayama, and meditation.

00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:35.110 align:middle line:10%
>> With over 38 million
followers in the US alone,

00:01:35.110 --> 00:01:37.750 align:middle line:10%
the physical
postures, or asanas,

00:01:37.750 --> 00:01:41.350 align:middle line:10%
of Hatha yoga make it the
most recognizable form of yoga

00:01:41.350 --> 00:01:42.490 align:middle line:10%
in the West.

00:01:42.490 --> 00:01:45.220 align:middle line:84%
Many beginners are
drawn to the relaxation

00:01:45.220 --> 00:01:48.790 align:middle line:84%
and perceived laid-back tone
of the classes over other yoga

00:01:48.790 --> 00:01:49.810 align:middle line:90%
styles.

00:01:49.810 --> 00:01:53.620 align:middle line:84%
But in India, Hatha yoga
has a very different appeal.

00:01:53.620 --> 00:01:58.480 align:middle line:90%


00:01:58.480 --> 00:02:02.080 align:middle line:84%
>> I was intrigued to discover
recently that in the West,

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:07.220 align:middle line:84%
Hatha yoga is seen as the easy,
relaxed postural practice.

00:02:07.220 --> 00:02:09.550 align:middle line:10%
Because the word
"Hatha" in Sanskrit,

00:02:09.550 --> 00:02:12.060 align:middle line:10%
and Hat in Hindi means
force, means hardcore.

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:13.990 align:middle line:90%
It really means hardcore.

00:02:13.990 --> 00:02:18.400 align:middle line:84%
>> Hardcore because the union
of prana, energy, and chitta,

00:02:18.400 --> 00:02:22.120 align:middle line:84%
mind, is meant to strike
and create friction in order

00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:24.250 align:middle line:90%
to generate heat.

00:02:24.250 --> 00:02:25.182 align:middle line:90%
>> Power is power.

00:02:25.182 --> 00:02:26.140 align:middle line:90%
It's kind of like fire.

00:02:26.140 --> 00:02:29.170 align:middle line:84%
You can use it to cook
food or burn down a house.

00:02:29.170 --> 00:02:32.365 align:middle line:84%
So the rituals,
they amass power.

00:02:32.365 --> 00:02:34.936 align:middle line:84%
>> It's whenever you want
anything more than anything

00:02:34.936 --> 00:02:37.060 align:middle line:84%
else in the world, and
you'll do anything to do it,

00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:39.940 align:middle line:84%
and you won't stop
until you get it.

00:02:39.940 --> 00:02:42.240 align:middle line:90%
That's what Hat means, Hatha.

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:43.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Legs should be straight.

00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:50.390 align:middle line:84%
Now extend the right hand,
and then go touch the floor.

00:02:50.390 --> 00:02:53.270 align:middle line:10%
>> To begin to understand
Hatha's seemingly dual

00:02:53.270 --> 00:02:57.020 align:middle line:10%
personality, it's important
to understand some of its rich

00:02:57.020 --> 00:02:57.830 align:middle line:10%
history.

00:02:57.830 --> 00:03:00.350 align:middle line:84%
>> My work trying to
contextualize the history

00:03:00.350 --> 00:03:03.380 align:middle line:84%
of Hatha yoga looks at the
different traditions and sects

00:03:03.380 --> 00:03:04.220 align:middle line:90%
that practiced it.

00:03:04.220 --> 00:03:07.100 align:middle line:10%
And received wisdom, received
history of Hatha yoga

00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:08.780 align:middle line:10%
is that this sect
called the Naths who

00:03:08.780 --> 00:03:10.114 align:middle line:10%
are responsible for all of it.

00:03:10.114 --> 00:03:11.780 align:middle line:10%
But actually, there
are other traditions

00:03:11.780 --> 00:03:15.110 align:middle line:10%
of yogis that are also equally
responsible for developing

00:03:15.110 --> 00:03:18.400 align:middle line:10%
and promoting the techniques
of Hatha yoga in their text.

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:21.290 align:middle line:84%
>> The practices of these
medieval movements offer

00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:23.465 align:middle line:84%
scholars clues on
Hatha's origins.

00:03:23.465 --> 00:03:26.030 align:middle line:90%


00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:29.210 align:middle line:84%
>> As I looked into it, I
realized that the only Sanskrit

00:03:29.210 --> 00:03:32.296 align:middle line:84%
text of any relevance to
these holy men, Babas--

00:03:32.296 --> 00:03:33.920 align:middle line:84%
and they have various
different names--

00:03:33.920 --> 00:03:36.690 align:middle line:84%
that I've been living with in
India are the ones on yoga,

00:03:36.690 --> 00:03:39.560 align:middle line:90%
in particular Hatha yoga.

00:03:39.560 --> 00:03:41.540 align:middle line:84%
The teachings of
yoga are originally

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:46.250 align:middle line:84%
developed by these renouncers,
these holy men whose lives you

00:03:46.250 --> 00:03:50.420 align:middle line:84%
or I can't aspire to emulate,
because they're the yogis par

00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:51.334 align:middle line:90%
excellence.

00:03:51.334 --> 00:03:53.000 align:middle line:84%
They're practicing
breathing techniques,

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:55.790 align:middle line:84%
sitting down in an
asana, meditating--

00:03:55.790 --> 00:03:58.705 align:middle line:84%
that's what they do 100% of
their time, 24 hours a day.

00:03:58.705 --> 00:04:01.130 align:middle line:90%
[SITAR PLAYING]

00:04:01.130 --> 00:04:04.050 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.050 --> 00:04:07.880 align:middle line:84%
>> These renouncers follow very
closely Patanjali's eight limb

00:04:07.880 --> 00:04:10.790 align:middle line:84%
structure, as outlined
in the Yoga Sutras,

00:04:10.790 --> 00:04:15.960 align:middle line:84%
the foremost detailed
exposition of all Yogic paths.

00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:20.450 align:middle line:10%
>> It's a very systematic
way to recognize the mind,

00:04:20.450 --> 00:04:23.390 align:middle line:10%
to purify the mind,
focus the mind,

00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:27.290 align:middle line:10%
and then ultimately learn how
to subdue or silence the mind

00:04:27.290 --> 00:04:30.300 align:middle line:10%
so we get an expanded awareness
and consciousness when our mind

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:31.100 align:middle line:10%
becomes quiet.

00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:34.130 align:middle line:90%


00:04:34.130 --> 00:04:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>> So to understand Hatha,
one must have a foundational

00:04:38.060 --> 00:04:41.540 align:middle line:84%
understanding of Patanjali's
eightfold path of techniques

00:04:41.540 --> 00:04:43.790 align:middle line:84%
designed to train
the body, mind,

00:04:43.790 --> 00:04:47.240 align:middle line:84%
and senses for
spiritual evolution.

00:04:47.240 --> 00:04:49.940 align:middle line:84%
While there are many ways
scholars reference the eight

00:04:49.940 --> 00:04:52.640 align:middle line:84%
limbs, they are simply
illustrated here

00:04:52.640 --> 00:04:56.090 align:middle line:84%
as the limbs of a tree that
build on each other for easier

00:04:56.090 --> 00:04:57.740 align:middle line:90%
understanding.

00:04:57.740 --> 00:05:01.460 align:middle line:84%
>> There have been beautiful,
beautiful books and teachings

00:05:01.460 --> 00:05:04.280 align:middle line:90%
on how they actually intertwine.

00:05:04.280 --> 00:05:07.670 align:middle line:10%
So I don't want to talk
about them as though they

00:05:07.670 --> 00:05:12.380 align:middle line:10%
were necessary states that one
had to go through sequentially

00:05:12.380 --> 00:05:14.030 align:middle line:10%
or hierarchically.

00:05:14.030 --> 00:05:16.580 align:middle line:84%
But it really does help
to think about them

00:05:16.580 --> 00:05:20.150 align:middle line:84%
and learn them like that, that
in many ways, each of the limbs

00:05:20.150 --> 00:05:23.510 align:middle line:84%
exists in each of
the other limbs.

00:05:23.510 --> 00:05:28.130 align:middle line:10%
Now, as anyone who's ever
tried to build anything knows,

00:05:28.130 --> 00:05:30.610 align:middle line:10%
you've got to have a foundation.

00:05:30.610 --> 00:05:34.700 align:middle line:84%
And the foundation of yoga
is what Sage Patanjali called

00:05:34.700 --> 00:05:36.020 align:middle line:90%
the yamas and the niyamas.

00:05:36.020 --> 00:05:38.720 align:middle line:90%


00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:42.340 align:middle line:84%
>> These ethical foundations are
laid out in the first two limbs

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:44.500 align:middle line:90%
of Patanjali's eightfold path.

00:05:44.500 --> 00:05:48.370 align:middle line:84%
The first limb holds the five
yamas, considered the great,

00:05:48.370 --> 00:05:52.330 align:middle line:84%
mighty, and universal vows to
be practiced on all levels--

00:05:52.330 --> 00:05:55.070 align:middle line:90%
actions, words, and thoughts.

00:05:55.070 --> 00:06:00.760 align:middle line:84%
>> The first skill is to
make nonviolence the baseline

00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:02.950 align:middle line:90%
for our decisions.

00:06:02.950 --> 00:06:06.280 align:middle line:84%
Then he says, put
every speech act

00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:08.950 align:middle line:84%
through the sieve
of truthfulness.

00:06:08.950 --> 00:06:11.420 align:middle line:84%
Use your words very,
very carefully.

00:06:11.420 --> 00:06:13.180 align:middle line:90%
Do I really need to say this?

00:06:13.180 --> 00:06:14.740 align:middle line:90%
How will I say this?

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:20.950 align:middle line:84%
How will my word give honor
to the ultimate existence?

00:06:20.950 --> 00:06:24.340 align:middle line:84%
And then the third
practice is not stealing.

00:06:24.340 --> 00:06:29.020 align:middle line:84%
How much feeds our greed
instead of our need?

00:06:29.020 --> 00:06:31.450 align:middle line:84%
The fourth practice
is brahmacharya,

00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:34.210 align:middle line:84%
and brahmacharya takes
two forms in India.

00:06:34.210 --> 00:06:37.640 align:middle line:84%
One is for the monks
and the nuns to abstain,

00:06:37.640 --> 00:06:40.660 align:middle line:84%
and the other is for
people to commit themselves

00:06:40.660 --> 00:06:44.380 align:middle line:84%
in a relationship and to
really honor that other person

00:06:44.380 --> 00:06:46.780 align:middle line:90%
as divinity.

00:06:46.780 --> 00:06:50.420 align:middle line:84%
And then the fifth vow
of non-possession, or not

00:06:50.420 --> 00:06:52.600 align:middle line:90%
take up more than we need.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:54.880 align:middle line:84%
That gives us a
place of freedom.

00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:58.000 align:middle line:90%


00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:01.810 align:middle line:84%
>> The next limb, the niyamas,
also has five leaves and are

00:07:01.810 --> 00:07:04.870 align:middle line:84%
considered things to
do, or observances.

00:07:04.870 --> 00:07:07.540 align:middle line:10%
>> It comes along with
a more positive way,

00:07:07.540 --> 00:07:10.450 align:middle line:10%
the second phase of yoga,
which are the niyamas.

00:07:10.450 --> 00:07:15.150 align:middle line:84%
And this says purify,
sauca, to clean yourself,

00:07:15.150 --> 00:07:19.300 align:middle line:84%
to clean your thoughts, to
be mindful, to eat pure food.

00:07:19.300 --> 00:07:23.140 align:middle line:84%
And then santosa-- to
develop contentment,

00:07:23.140 --> 00:07:26.770 align:middle line:84%
to say let's appreciate
every morning.

00:07:26.770 --> 00:07:30.370 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's a cloudy
day-- we need the rain.

00:07:30.370 --> 00:07:33.250 align:middle line:84%
If it's a sunny
day, how beautiful.

00:07:33.250 --> 00:07:35.200 align:middle line:90%
And then the third is tapas.

00:07:35.200 --> 00:07:39.160 align:middle line:84%
The idea is that it's
the difficulty that

00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:40.990 align:middle line:90%
strengthens our character.

00:07:40.990 --> 00:07:43.620 align:middle line:10%
Then this leads
naturally into svadhyaya,

00:07:43.620 --> 00:07:47.000 align:middle line:10%
a sense of self-cultivation
through study.

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.050 align:middle line:10%
The final is isvara
pranidhana-- to have

00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:53.110 align:middle line:10%
an idea of something
that is wonderful

00:07:53.110 --> 00:07:56.950 align:middle line:10%
and a person that is wonderful,
and as Maya Angelou said,

00:07:56.950 --> 00:08:00.550 align:middle line:10%
to work every day at
becoming our best self.

00:08:00.550 --> 00:08:07.750 align:middle line:90%


00:08:07.750 --> 00:08:11.210 align:middle line:10%
>> The next three limbs are
quite practical in nature,

00:08:11.210 --> 00:08:15.850 align:middle line:10%
the first being asana, which
in this context means posture.

00:08:15.850 --> 00:08:18.700 align:middle line:90%
>> Where do our problems reside?

00:08:18.700 --> 00:08:22.450 align:middle line:84%
They're going to show up in
the body, in the tightness,

00:08:22.450 --> 00:08:30.100 align:middle line:84%
in the rigidity, and in some
instances in the over-fluidity.

00:08:30.100 --> 00:08:35.100 align:middle line:84%
The moving into pranayama is
the quieting of the breath.

00:08:35.100 --> 00:08:40.350 align:middle line:10%
Sit, calm yourself,
breathe, and let

00:08:40.350 --> 00:08:45.110 align:middle line:10%
yourself turn inward to move
into that fifth phase of yoga.

00:08:45.110 --> 00:08:47.240 align:middle line:10%
And that fifth phase
of yoga is called

00:08:47.240 --> 00:08:50.460 align:middle line:10%
pratyahara, which is
that place of inwardness,

00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:55.410 align:middle line:10%
to be able to position
yourself to truly move

00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:59.310 align:middle line:10%
into a state of holding.

00:08:59.310 --> 00:09:02.430 align:middle line:10%
>> The final three limbs
describe a deepening meditative

00:09:02.430 --> 00:09:06.780 align:middle line:10%
state culminating in samadhi,
a state of complete absorption

00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:08.730 align:middle line:10%
with infinite spirit.

00:09:08.730 --> 00:09:11.910 align:middle line:84%
>> The sixth level of
yoga is called dharana,

00:09:11.910 --> 00:09:14.700 align:middle line:90%
and it literally means holding.

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:18.570 align:middle line:84%
And these dharanas
build into meditation

00:09:18.570 --> 00:09:23.580 align:middle line:84%
where whatever your focus,
we're able to place ourselves

00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:26.390 align:middle line:84%
for a sustained period
through the quieting

00:09:26.390 --> 00:09:27.720 align:middle line:90%
of the body and the breath.

00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:31.260 align:middle line:84%
And that meditation
then informs everything

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:33.100 align:middle line:90%
that we do throughout the day.

00:09:33.100 --> 00:09:36.300 align:middle line:84%
So the eighth limb
of yoga is samadhi,

00:09:36.300 --> 00:09:40.170 align:middle line:84%
that place of being totally
absorbed, being totally well.

00:09:40.170 --> 00:09:42.810 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter what you're
doing, but you're present,

00:09:42.810 --> 00:09:46.500 align:middle line:84%
and you're in a
place of exuberance.

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:50.220 align:middle line:84%
You have everything
that you need.

00:09:50.220 --> 00:09:51.020 align:middle line:90%
And that's yoga.

00:09:51.020 --> 00:09:54.800 align:middle line:90%


00:09:54.800 --> 00:09:58.310 align:middle line:84%
>> While samadhi is the
aim of all Yogic paths,

00:09:58.310 --> 00:10:02.190 align:middle line:84%
it is not easily attained and
can take a lifetime to achieve,

00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:02.990 align:middle line:90%
if at all.

00:10:02.990 --> 00:10:09.980 align:middle line:90%


00:10:09.980 --> 00:10:12.950 align:middle line:10%
So Hatha yoga, as
stated in the sutras,

00:10:12.950 --> 00:10:15.800 align:middle line:10%
was meant as a total
life philosophy,

00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:19.190 align:middle line:10%
its steady and comfortable
asanas meant as a path

00:10:19.190 --> 00:10:22.580 align:middle line:10%
to achieve mastery of the
mind so that self-realization

00:10:22.580 --> 00:10:25.380 align:middle line:10%
can be experienced.

00:10:25.380 --> 00:10:28.230 align:middle line:10%
>> At least 2,000 years ago,
you start seeing the Buddha

00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:33.360 align:middle line:10%
and the Jain saints in Lotus
position and other postures

00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:37.830 align:middle line:10%
that provide a kind of steady,
solid base for meditation.

00:10:37.830 --> 00:10:40.870 align:middle line:84%
The way yoga is understood
in those early texts

00:10:40.870 --> 00:10:43.350 align:middle line:84%
is a way of just completely
stilling the body

00:10:43.350 --> 00:10:45.180 align:middle line:90%
and stilling the mind.

00:10:45.180 --> 00:10:47.940 align:middle line:10%
So anything that is
uncomfortable can

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:49.620 align:middle line:10%
be held indefinitely
is really not

00:10:49.620 --> 00:10:54.330 align:middle line:10%
going to wash in that context.

00:10:54.330 --> 00:10:57.180 align:middle line:84%
>> A prime example
of a classic asana,

00:10:57.180 --> 00:11:00.600 align:middle line:84%
meant to still the body in order
to still the mind and increase

00:11:00.600 --> 00:11:03.040 align:middle line:90%
focus, is the Headstand.

00:11:03.040 --> 00:11:06.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, there's this notion
central to the first Hatha yoga

00:11:06.210 --> 00:11:08.340 align:middle line:90%
text that--

00:11:08.340 --> 00:11:10.710 align:middle line:84%
they're all written from
the point of view of men--

00:11:10.710 --> 00:11:13.560 align:middle line:84%
that in men, there's this
substance called bindu

00:11:13.560 --> 00:11:15.000 align:middle line:90%
which is produced in the head.

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:17.160 align:middle line:84%
And it's constantly
dripping down

00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:19.560 align:middle line:84%
and either being
ejaculated as semen

00:11:19.560 --> 00:11:22.466 align:middle line:84%
or being burnt up by
fire in the stomach.

00:11:22.466 --> 00:11:24.840 align:middle line:84%
And then there are these
various methods of stopping that

00:11:24.840 --> 00:11:25.870 align:middle line:90%
from happening.

00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:28.480 align:middle line:10%
The most crude, basic,
obvious one is the Headstand.

00:11:28.480 --> 00:11:29.280 align:middle line:90%
You use gravity.

00:11:29.280 --> 00:11:32.610 align:middle line:84%
If you stand on your
head, then gravity

00:11:32.610 --> 00:11:35.227 align:middle line:84%
will stop it from dripping
down and being burnt up.

00:11:35.227 --> 00:11:36.810 align:middle line:84%
And the idea is that
in normal people,

00:11:36.810 --> 00:11:38.420 align:middle line:84%
it's constantly
being wasted away.

00:11:38.420 --> 00:11:41.550 align:middle line:84%
And that's the process that
brings about old age and death.

00:11:41.550 --> 00:11:45.630 align:middle line:84%
But yogis can stop that process,
and thereby, often the text

00:11:45.630 --> 00:11:48.510 align:middle line:90%
will say, remain immortal.

00:11:48.510 --> 00:11:53.930 align:middle line:84%
Through these various practices,
you can achieve enlightenment.

00:11:53.930 --> 00:11:56.310 align:middle line:84%
